SIMPLE: pilose
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pilose
<hw>Pi*lose"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pilosus</ets>, fr. <ets>pilus</ets> hair. See <er>Pile</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Hairy; full of, or made of, hair.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The heat-retaining property of the <qex>pilose</qex> covering.</q>
<rj><qau>Owen.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Clothed thickly with pile or soft
down.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Covered with long, slender hairs;
resembling long hairs; hairy; <as>as, <ex>pilose</ex>
pubescence</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pilosity</ent>⟦br⟧
